@Wayne on group identity: this is an approach to the immense problem I have with xmin. It seems to pretend a naivete that even children do not have, rendering it remarkably impractical. 

It's also hard to reconcile the spirit of xmin with threads like "Slippery Slope?"

We have our articles of identity. They complicate everything. They are everything.

@wayno. I wish I could say it like that -- perhaps less the rancor for the mass media meat machine, which has made me what I am today.

But you must understand that Chad has to, as he famously wrote once, "save tons of people" (cf. Item 12c, http://dev.music.flanderous.com/part/886) -- the inescapable mission of Christianity.

In lieu of the messy, ineffective, resource-consuming ministry we have all put off for some reason or another, one could use one's supernatant hours to design a sort of "killer app" "viral Christianity," able to effectively save  a broad host range with minimal growth outlay.
